an cyclone seasons: [[2018 North Indian Ocean cyclone season|2018]], [[2019 North Indian Ocean cyclone season|2019]]\n*[[2018\u201319 Australian region cyclone season]]\n*[[2018\u201319 South Pacific cyclone season]]\n*[[1999\u20132000 South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season]] \u2013 The third-deadliest South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|2018-19 South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season}}\n* [http://www.meteofrance.re M\u00e9t\u00e9o-France La R\u00e9union] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.meteomadagascar.mg Direction G\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la M\u00e9t\u00e9orologie de Madagascar] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://metservice.intnet.mu Mauritius Meteorological Services]\n* [http://www.metoc.navy.mil/jtwc/jtwc.html Joint Typhoon Warning Center (JTWC)]\n\n{{2018\u201319 South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season buttons}}\n{{TC Decades|Year=2010|basin=South-West Indian Ocean|type=cyclone|shem=yes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2018-19 South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season}}\n[[Category:2018\u201319 South-West Indian Ocean cyclone season]]\n[[Category:South-West Indian Ocean cyclone seasons]]\n", "name_user": "NotYourFriend 420", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eModerate Tropical Storm 01", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018%E2%80%9319_South-West_Indian_Ocean_cyclone_season"}
{"title_page": "Theophilus Fortescue", "text_new": "'''Theophilus Fortescue''' (1707\u20131746), of [[Castle Hill, Filleigh]], near Barnstaple, Devon, was a British Whig politician who sat in the [[British House of Commons|House of Commons]] from 1727 to 1746.\n\nFortescue was the third son of [[Hugh Fortescue (1665\u20131719)|Hugh Fortescue]], MP of [[Filleigh]] and his first wife Bridget Boscawen, daughter of [[Hugh Boscawen (1625\u20131701)|Hugh Boscawen]] of Tregothnan, Cornwall. <ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url =https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/fortescue-theophilus-1707-1746  | title= FORTESCUE, Theophilus (c.1707-1746), of Castle Hill, Filleigh, nr. Barnstaple, Devon.| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 1 February 2019 }}</ref >.\n \nFortescue was returned unopposed as an opposition Whig [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Barnstaple (UK Parliament constituency)|Barnstaple]] on his family's interest at the [[1727 British general election]]. He voted against the Administration in almost every division. He was returned for Barnstaple unopposed again at the  [[1734 British general election]]. At the [[1741 British general election]]  he transferred to [[Devon (UK Parliament constituency)|Devon]] where he was returned unopposed.<ref name=HOP/>\n\nFortescue died unmarried on 13 March 1746.<ref name=HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[Thomas Whetham|Lieutenant-General Thomas Whetham]]\n | before2 = [[Sir Hugh Acland, 6th Baronet|Sir Hugh Acland]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title =  [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Barnstaple (UK Parliament constituency)|Barnstaple]]\n | years =   [[1727 British general election|1727]]\u2013[[1741 British general election|1741]]\n | with  =  [[Richard Coffin (1684-1766)|Richard Coffin]] 1727-1734\n | with2 = [[Sir John Chichester, 4th Baronet|Sir John Chichester]] 1734-1740\n | with3 = [[John Basset (died 1757)|John Basset]] 1740-1741\n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[John Harris (1703-1768)|John Harris]]\n | after2 = [[Henry Rolle, 1st Baron Rolle|Henry Rolle]]\n}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[John Bampfylde (1691\u20131750)|John Bampfylde]]\n | before2 = [[Henry Rolle, 1st Baron Rolle|Henry Rolle]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title =  [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Devon (UK Parliament constituency)|Devon]]\n | years =   [[1741 British general election|1741]]\u20131746   \n | with  =  [[William Courtenay, 1st Viscount Courtenay|Sir William Courtenay, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[William Courtenay, 1st Viscount Courtenay|Sir William Courtenay, Bt]]\n | after2 = [[Sir Thomas Dyke Acland, 7th Baronet|Sir Thomas Dyke-Acland, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fortescue, Theophilus }}\n[[Category:1707 births]]\n[[Category:1746 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n [[Category:British MPs 1727\u20131734]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1734\u20131741]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1741\u20131747]]\n", "text_old": "'''Theophilus Fortescue''' (1707\u20131746), of [[Castle Hill, Filleigh]], near Barnstaple, Devon, was a British Whig politician who sat in the [[British House of Commons|House of Commons]] from 1727 to 1746.\n\nFortescue was the third son of [[Hugh Fortescue (1665\u20131719)|Hugh Fortescue]], MP of [[Filleigh]] and his first wife Bridget Boscawen, daughter of [[Hugh Boscawen (1625\u20131701)|Hugh Boscawen]] of Tregothnan, Cornwall. <ref name = HOP>{{cite web| url =https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/fortescue-theophilus-1707-1746  | title= FORTESCUE, Theophilus (c.1707-1746), of Castle Hill, Filleigh, nr. Barnstaple, Devon.| publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 1 February 2019 }}</ref >.\n \nFortescue was returned unopposed as an opposition Whig [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Barnstaple (UK Parliament constituency)|Barnstaple]] on his family\u2019s interest at the [[1727 British general election]]. He voted against the Administration in almost every division. He was returned for Barnstaple unopposed again at the  [[1734 British general election]]. At the [[1741 British general election]]  he transferred to [[Devon (UK Parliament constituency)|Devon]] where he was returned unopposed.<ref name=HOP/>\n\nFortescue died unmarried on 13 March 1746.<ref name=HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[Thomas Whetham|Lieutenant-General Thomas Whetham]]\n | before2 = [[Sir Hugh Acland, 6th Baronet|Sir Hugh Acland]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title =  [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Barnstaple (UK Parliament constituency)|Barnstaple]]\n | years =   [[1727 British general election|1727]]\u2013[[1741 British general election|1741]]\n | with  =  [[Richard Coffin (1684-1766)|Richard Coffin]] 1727-1734\n | with2 = [[Sir John Chichester, 4th Baronet|Sir John Chichester]] 1734-1740\n | with3 = [[John Basset (died 1757)|John Basset]] 1740-1741\n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[John Harris (1703-1768)|John Harris]]\n | after2 = [[Henry Rolle, 1st Baron Rolle|Henry Rolle]]\n}}\n{{s-bef\n | before  = [[John Bampfylde (1691\u20131750)|John Bampfylde]]\n | before2 = [[Henry Rolle, 1st Baron Rolle|Henry Rolle]]\n}}\n{{s-title\n | title =  [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Devon (UK Parliament constituency)|Devon]]\n | years =   [[1741 British general election|1741]]\u20131746   \n | with  =  [[William Courtenay, 1st Viscount Courtenay|Sir William Courtenay, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-aft\n | after  = [[William Courtenay, 1st Viscount Courtenay|Sir William Courtenay, Bt]]\n | after2 = [[Sir Thomas Dyke Acland, 7th Baronet|Sir Thomas Dyke-Acland, Bt]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fortescue, Theophilus }}\n[[Category:1707 births]]\n[[Category:1746 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n [[Category:British MPs 1727\u20131734]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1734\u20131741]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1741\u20131747]]\n", "name_user": "J947", "