our DNA Genealogy |language= ru |location= \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430 |publisher=\u041a\u043e\u043d\u0446\u0435\u043f\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043b |year=2016 |isbn=978-5-9067-5698-5}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Klyosov |first1= A. A. |title=\u0414\u041d\u041a-\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u0410 \u0434\u043e \u0422 |trans-title= DNA Genealogy from A to T |language= ru |location= \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430 |publisher=\u041a\u043d\u0438\u0436\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043c\u0438\u0440 |year=2016 |isbn=978-5-8041-0873-2}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://anatole-klyosov.com/ Klyosov's home page]\n* [http://www.themoscowtimes.com/business/article/one-of-russias-first-internet-users-recalls-the-thrill/409068.html One of Russia's First Internet Users Recalls the Thrill]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Klyosov, Anatole}}\n[[Category:Genetic genealogy]]\n[[Category:Russian genealogists]]\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian physical chemists]]\n[[Category:Pseudohistorians]]\n", "name_user": "Pudu\u1e2bepa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anatole_Klyosov"}
{"title_page": "St Joseph\u2019s Higher Secondary School, Baramulla", "text_new": "{{primary sources|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2011}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name = St. Joseph\u2019s Higher Secondary School\n| image = SJS Baramulla.jpg\n| motto = Manners Maketh Man\n| streetaddress = Opp. Head Post Office\n| city = [[Baramulla]]\n| state = [[Kashmir]] J&K\n| country = India\n| coordinates = {{Coord|34.203512|N|74.350305|E|display=title}}\n| schooltype = [[Private school|Private]]\n| type = Missionary\n| religious_affiliation = Catholic Christian\n| patron = [[St. Joseph]]\n| established = {{start date and age|1905}}\n| founded = 1903\n| founder = Fr. C. B. Simons [[Mill Hill Missionaries|MHM]]\n| status = Active\n| administrator = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu\u2013Srinagar]]\n| principal = Rev. fr. Antony Peppin\n| headmistress = Sr. Prabha CMC\n| faculty = Local\n| gender = Co-Educational\n| classes = Class Nursery  \u2013 12th\n| hours_in_day = 6<sup>Hr</sup>\n| classrooms = 150+\n| houses = Peace, Grace, Joy and Wisdom\n| colours = Blue, Green, Red, Yellow (All classes), Orange (Primary only)\n| sports = Football, Cricket, Volleyball, Basketball, kho-kho, Badminton, Athletics,hockey\n| nickname = Josephites\n| campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n| postalcode = 193101\n| school_board = [[Jammu and Kashmir State Board of School Education|J & K Board of School Education]]\n| language = English\n| students = 4000+\n| homepage = http://www.sjskashmir.org\n}}\n\n'''St. Joseph\u2019s Higher Secondary School Baramulla''' (commonly referred to as the '''St. Josephs School Baramulla''' or '''SJS''') is a private school located in [[Baramulla]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. The school has been upgraded to the status of a higher secondary school and has also started online education, the first in the Kashmir valley.<ref>[http://sjskashmir.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=58&Itemid=88 History]</ref><ref>[http://www.schoolsworld.in/schools/showschool.php?school_id=1020204604]</ref> St. Josephs School is located in the city of [[Baramulla]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. It has around 3,500 students and over 115 staff members.<ref>http://www.sjskashmir.org/staff.php</ref> It is considered to be one of the oldes schools in the kashmir valley.\n\nThe school was founded by the [[Herbert Vaughan|Mill Hill Fathers]] or [[Mill Hill Missionaries]] from [[London]] in 1903, owned by the [[Catholicism|Catholic]] [[Diocese]] of [[Jammu]]-[[Srinagar]] and is administered by its Education Society (Reg. No. 1601-S of 1989) under the provisions of article 30(1) of the [[Constitution]]; for everyone without any distinction of religion, caste, creed or colour.<ref>[http://sjskashmir.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=60&Itemid=89 Overview]</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nThe foundation of St. Josephs School Baramulla was laid by Father C. Simon, in late 18th century and eventually in 1903 he established the school.<ref name=\"Hambye1982\">{{cite book|author=Edward Ren\u00e9 Hambye|title=The St. Thomas Christian encyclopaedia of India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eQ3ZAAAAMAAJ|year=1982|publisher=St. Thomas Christian Encyclopaedia of India}}</ref> St. Joseph's School is one of the oldest missionary schools in [[Kashmir Valley|Kashmir valley]]. The school was founded and run by [[Saint Joseph's Missionary Society of Mill Hill]] as a Boarding school initially. It was run by [[Society of Jesus|Society Of Jesus]] after [[Saint Joseph's Missionary Society of Mill Hill|Mill Hill Missionaries]] left the mission.\n\n==Alumni==\n* [[Maqbool Bhat]]- Kashmiri Revolutionary Leader,Journalist,author,philosopher,humanist and founder of National Liberation Front(NLF)and then declared leader of Jammu Kashmir Liberation Front(JKLF).<ref>https://www.newsclick.in/kashmir-observes-shutdown-death-anniversary-maqbool-bhat</ref><ref>https://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/kashmir/azadi-demands-sacrifices-says-maqbool-bhat-s-mother/113465.html</ref><ref>http://www.kashmirink.in/news/currentissue/remembering-maqbool-bhatt-from-birth-to-execution/273.html</ref>\n* [[Mohammad Najibullah]] - Afghan President  <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldpresidentsdb.com/Mohammad-Najibullah/|title=Mohammad Najibullah - President of Afghanistan|website=www.worldpresidentsdb.com|access-date=2017-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Udb1AQAAQBAJ&pg=PA509|title=A Concise History of Afghanistan in 25 Volumes: Volume 1|last=Alikuzai|first=Hamid Wahed|date=2013-10-11|publisher=Trafford Publishing|isbn=9781490714479|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Syed Altaf Bukhari]] - Indian Politician<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/sports/sports-meet-concludes-at-st-joseph-s-baramulla/193904.html|title=Sports meet concludes at St Joseph's Baramulla|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Muhammad Ashraf Bukhari]] - Bureaucrat<ref>http://jkgad.nic.in/gadDynamic/FormerAdmSecretaries.aspx</ref>\n*[[Muhammad Yusuf Saraf]]- Chief Justice of the Azad Kashmir High Court <ref>{{Cite web | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Kashmiris_Fight_for_Freedom.html?id=_egBAAAAMAAJ |title = Kashmiris Fight for Freedom|last1 = Saraf|first1 = Muhammad Yusuf|year = 1977}}</ref><ref>https://m.greaterkashmir.com/news/gk-magazine/kashmir-nearest-to-his-heart/173795.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://sjskashmir.com/index.php Official website]\n\n== See also ==\n[[List of schools in India|List of Schools in India]]\n\n[[List of Christian schools in India|List of Christian Schools in India]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint Joseph's School (Baramulla)}}\n[[Category:Private schools in Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Christian schools in Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1901]]\n[[Category:1901 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Baramulla]]\n[[Category:Catholic schools in India]]\n[[Category:Schools founded by missionaries]]\n", "text_old": "{{primary sources|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2011}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name = St. Joseph\u2019s Higher Secondary School\n| image = SJS Baramulla.jpg\n| motto = Manners Maketh Man\n| streetaddress = Opp. Head Post Office\n| city = [[Baramulla]]\n| state = [[Kashmir]] J&K\n| country = India\n| coordinates = {{Coord|34.203512|N|74.350305|E|display=title}}\n| schooltype = [[Private school|Private]]\n| type = Missionary\n| religious_affiliation = Catholic Christian\n| patron = [[St. Joseph]]\n| established = {{start date and age|1905}}\n| founded = 1903\n| founder = Fr. C. B. Simons [[Mill Hill Missionaries|MHM]]\n| status = Active\n| administrator = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu\u2013Srinagar]]\n| principal = Rev. fr. Antony Peppin\n| headmistress = Sr. Prabha CMC\n| faculty = Local\n| gender = Co-Educational\n| classes = Class Nursery  \u2013 12th\n| hours_in_day = 6<sup>Hr</sup>\n| classrooms = 150+\n| houses = Peace, Grace, Joy and Wisdom\n| colours = Blue, Green, Red, Yellow (All classes), Orange (Primary only)\n| sports = Football, Cricket, Volleyball, Basketball, kho-kho, Badminton, Athletics,hockey\n| nickname = Josephites\n| campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n| postalcode = 193101\n| school_board = [[Jammu and Kashmir State Board of School Education|J & K Board of School Education]]\n| language = English\n| students = 4000+\n| homepage = http://www.sjskashmir.org\n}}\n\n'''St. Joseph\u2019s Higher Secondary School Baramulla''' (commonly referred to as the '''St. Josephs School Baramulla''' or '''SJS''') is a private school located in [[Baramulla]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. The school has been upgraded to the status of a higher secondary school and has also started online education, the first in the Kashmir valley.<ref>[http://sjskashmir.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=58&Itemid=88 History]</ref><ref>[http://www.schoolsworld.in/schools/showschool.php?school_id=1020204604]</ref> St. Josephs School is located in the city of [[Baramulla]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. It has around 3,500 students and over 115 staff members.<ref>http://www.sjskashmir.org/staff.php</ref>\n\nThe school was founded by the [[Herbert Vaughan|Mill Hill Fathers]] or [[Mill Hill Missionaries]] from [[London]] in 1903, owned by the [[Catholicism|Catholic]] [[Diocese]] of [[Jammu]]-[[Srinagar]] and is administered by its Education Society (Reg. No. 1601-S of 1989) under the provisions of article 30(1) of the [[Constitution]]; for everyone without any distinction of religion, caste, creed or colour.<ref>[http://sjskashmir.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=60&Itemid=89 Overview]</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nThe foundation of St. Josephs School Baramulla was laid by Father C. Simon, in late 18th century and eventually in 1903 he established the school.<ref name=\"Hambye1982\">{{cite book|author=Edward Ren\u00e9 Hambye|title=The St. Thomas Christian encyclopaedia of India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eQ3ZAAAAMAAJ|year=1982|publisher=St. Thomas Christian Encyclopaedia of India}}</ref> St. Joseph's School is one of the oldest missionary schools in [[Kashmir Valley|Kashmir valley]]. The school was founded and run by [[Saint Joseph's Missionary Society of Mill Hill]] as a Boarding school initially. It was run by [[Society of Jesus|Society Of Jesus]] after [[Saint Joseph's Missionary Society of Mill Hill|Mill Hill Missionaries]] left the mission.\n\n==Alumni==\n* [[Maqbool Bhat]]- Kashmiri Revolutionary Leader,Journalist,author,philosopher,humanist and founder of National Liberation Front(NLF)and then declared leader of Jammu Kashmir Liberation Front(JKLF).<ref>https://www.newsclick.in/kashmir-observes-shutdown-death-anniversary-maqbool-bhat</ref><ref>https://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/kashmir/azadi-demands-sacrifices-says-maqbool-bhat-s-mother/113465.html</ref><ref>http://www.kashmirink.in/news/currentissue/remembering-maqbool-bhatt-from-birth-to-execution/273.html</ref>\n* [[Mohammad Najibullah]] - Afghan President  <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldpresidentsdb.com/Mohammad-Najibullah/|title=Mohammad Najibullah - President of Afghanistan|website=www.worldpresidentsdb.com|access-date=2017-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Udb1AQAAQBAJ&pg=PA509|title=A Concise History of Afghanistan in 25 Volumes: Volume 1|last=Alikuzai|first=Hamid Wahed|date=2013-10-11|publisher=Trafford Publishing|isbn=9781490714479|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Syed Altaf Bukhari]] - Indian Politician<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/sports/sports-meet-concludes-at-st-joseph-s-baramulla/193904.html|title=Sports meet concludes at St Joseph's Baramulla|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Muhammad Ashraf Bukhari]] - Bureaucrat<ref>http://jkgad.nic.in/gadDynamic/FormerAdmSecretaries.aspx</ref>\n*[[Muhammad Yusuf Saraf]]- Chief Justice of the Azad Kashmir High Court <ref>{{Cite web | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Kashmiris_Fight_for_Freedom.html?id=_egBAAAAMAAJ |title = Kashmiris Fight for Freedom|last1 = Saraf|first1 = Muhammad Yusuf|year = 1977}}</ref><ref>https://m.greaterkashmir.com/news/gk-magazine/kashmir-nearest-to-his-heart/173795.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://sjskashmir.com/index.php Official website]\n\n== See also ==\n[[List of schools in India|List of Schools in India]]\n\n[[List of Christian schools in India|List of Christian Schools in India]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint Joseph's School (Baramulla)}}\n[[Category:Private schools in Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Christian schools in Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1901]]\n[[Category:1901 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Baramulla]]\n[[Category:Catholic schools in India]]\n[[Category:Schools founded by missionaries]]\n", "name_user": "2405:205:b00e:9612: